main event: In Pensacola, Florida, on 14 August 1966, an observer reported seeing a solid, self-luminous object resembling a white ping-pong ball with one black stripe.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 30 seconds,Appeared to be a solid body with no sound,The object could have been a cluster of balloons according to the conclusion,The witness reported a clear sky during the sighting,Despite some ambiguity, there were no photographs taken of the sighting.
sighted object: a solid, self-luminous body resembling a ping-pong ball
witness description: A male observer, age 34, who expressed confidence that what he saw was not a figment of his imagination.
